       fhir:ElementDefinition.comment [ fhir:value "If a composition is marked as withdrawn, the compositions/documents in the series, or data from the composition or document series, should never be displayed to a user without being clearly marked as untrustworthy. The flag \"entered-in-error\" is why this element is labeled as a modifier of other elements.   \n\nSome reporting work flows require that the original narrative of a final document never be altered; instead, only new narrative can be added. The composition resource has no explicit status for explicitly noting whether this business rule is in effect. This would be handled by an extension if required." ] ;
